<h1 id="pngjs" tabindex="-1"><a class="header-anchor" href="#pngjs"><span>pngjs</span></a></h1>
<p>Simple PNG encoder/decoder for Node.js with no dependencies.</p>
<p>Based on the original <a href="https://github.com/niegowski/node-pngjs" target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">pngjs</a> with the follow enhancements.</p>
<ul>
<li>Support for reading 1,2,4 &amp; 16 bit files</li>
<li>Support for reading interlace files</li>
<li>Support for reading <code v-pre>tTRNS</code> transparent colours</li>
<li>Support for writing colortype 0 (grayscale), colortype 2 (RGB), colortype 4 (grayscale alpha) and colortype 6 (RGBA)</li>
<li>Sync interface as well as async</li>
<li>API compatible with pngjs and node-pngjs</li>
</ul>
<p>Known lack of support for:</p>
<ul>
<li>Extended PNG e.g. Animation</li>
<li>Writing in colortype 3 (indexed color)</li>
</ul>
